<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p>On the <span class="Emphasis">Setup</span> tab of the Skin Editor, you can set the main menu position to <span class="Emphasis">Top</span>, <span class="Emphasis">Left</span>, or <span class="Emphasis">Right</span>. This is the primary menu (links to topics) that is based on your TOC when the output is being viewed on a large screen (not tablet or mobile). In a new<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> Side</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> Top</MadCap:conditionalText> Navigation skin, this field is set to<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> Left</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> Top</MadCap:conditionalText> by default, meaning the main menu will be placed<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> on the left side</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> at the top</MadCap:conditionalText> of the screen.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> However, you can change it to Right if you want the menu shown on the other side of the screen. If you choose Top, you will no longer be using a Side Navigation skin, but rather a Top Navigation skin, where the main menu is positioned at the top of the screen.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> If you choose Left or Right, you will no longer be using a Top Navigation skin, but rather a Side Navigation skin, where the main menu is positioned at the left or right side of the screen.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
</html>